      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC4c566b582b7810058adeae901b54fbd2"></a>Overhauling the rear swinging arm
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8186"> </a>Inside the swingarm (3), in correspondence with the pivot point on the frame, there is a pair of ball bearings (13) and a
            spacer (14) on the RH side, and a pair of needle roller bearings (15), with sealing rings (16), on the LH side.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_028103423.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_028203424.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_028303425.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8195"> </a>To change the bearings, proceed as follows.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8197"> </a>Remove the spacers (17) and (18) fitted on the RH side of the swingarm, and the bush (19) on the LH side.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8199"> </a>Remove the ball bearings (13), the sealing rings (16) and the needle roller bearings (15) with a suitable drift and press.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8201"> </a>Duly support the swinging arm and pay utmost attention to avoid damaging the seats during removal of these parts.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/important.jpg">Important
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8204"> </a>Once removed, the used bearings, seals and needle roller bearings must not be refitted.
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_028403426.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8209"> </a>Heat the entire swinging arm up to 150&nbsp;°C while supporting its weight adequately.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8211"> </a>Insert the new needle roller bearings (15) in the drift tool (A) no. <span class="bold">88713.1068</span>, and install them into the bore on the left-hand side of the swingarm, working from the outside.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8216"> </a>Drive them inside until the tool is fully seated against the swinging arm.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8218"> </a>Use the same tool to fit the new sealing rings (16), positioned as shown in the sectional view, so that they seat against
            the newly installed needle roller bearings.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_028503427.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_028603428.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8226"> </a>To install the ball bearings (13) you will need the tool no. <span class="bold">88713.2409</span> with:
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8231"> </a>(C) – drift for internal bearing;
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8233"> </a>(D) – drift for external bearing;
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8235"> </a>(E) – guide pin.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8238"> </a>Fit a new bearing (13) and the internal spacer (14) onto the drift (C) and install it on the inner side of the swingarm RH
            mounting.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8240"> </a>Insert the guide pin (E) into the previously mounted needle roller bearings and insert the other end in the bore in the drift
            (C).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8242"> </a>Drive the bearing (13) fully into the swinging arm. Fit the other new bearing (13) at the outer end of drift (C).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8244"> </a>Using drift (C) as a stop, use drift (D) to drive the external bearing against the spacer (14): remove the tools.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8246"> </a>Before refitting the swingarm (3), grease the ball bearings (13), the needle roller bearings (15) and the sealing rings (16)
            with the recommended grease.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_028703429.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_028803430.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8253"> </a>Refit the spacers (17) and (18) on the right-hand side of the swingarm (3) and refit the bush (19) on the left-hand side.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_028903431.jpg"></center>
      </div>
